
    Kim Porter, mother to three of Diddy's children, dies aged 47

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 Getty Images
                
            
            
        Kim Porter, who was mother to three of Diddy's children, has died aged 47. The model and actress dated the American rapper on and off from 1994 to 2007 and they had three children together: twins Jessie James and D'Lila, 11, and son Christian, 20. She also had a 27-year-old son, Quincy, from a previous marriage - it's not known how she died.Celebrities including Rihanna, 50 Cent and Missy Elliott have been paying tribute to her on social media.
    
        
